The paper proposes a system for automatically specializing mobile apps based on user preferences, which involves learning the quality of user experience under different reductions. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) and Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves active learning techniques, which could fall under the Programming Languages (cs.PL) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with resource usage and optimization, which could also fall under the Systems and Control (cs.SD) sub-category.
